FBIS4-8768 "dreeu074_i_94041" FBIS-EEU-94-074 Daily Report 18 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Events in Gorazde -- 18 April Events in Gorazde -- 18 April Hospital, Red Cross Hit AU1804082194 Paris AFP in English 0810 GMT 18 Apr 94 AU1804082194 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Geneva, April 18 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serbs resumed intensive shelling Monday [18 April] on the Moslem enclave of Gorazde in eastern Bosnia, hitting the hospital roof and Red Cross centre, a UN spokeswoman said here. "The night was quiet, but gunfire started again this morning," said Sylvana Foa, spokeswoman for the UN High Commissioner for Refugees. A shell was falling every 20 seconds, she said. "The hospital was hit on the roof," she said, adding that the International Committee of the Red Cross centre in the town was also hit.
